Explanation:

The solution iterates through the input array `nums` using a for-each loop. For each element, it adds the element to the running sum `sum`. If the sum is not a multiple of `k`, it means there is no subarray with the desired property, so the function returns `false`. Otherwise, it divides the sum by `k` to update the running sum for the next iteration. Since the array has `n` elements, the time complexity is O(n). The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a single variable `sum` and do not require any additional data structures.

